subject: Volleyball
College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Penn State, the defending champion, and Stanford, runner-up the last two years, survived five-set semifinals Thursday to advance to a rematch for the N.C.A.A title in women’s volleyball. The Nittany Lions lost their first two sets of the year but improved to 37-0 with a victory over Nebraska. The Cardinal (31-3) defeated Texas to advance to the title match for a record 14th time.
